{"lemma":"بَطَلَ","slug":"بَطَلَ","root":"ب.ط.ل","root_slug":"ب-ط-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ط-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"بَطَلَ","root":"بطل","pos":"V","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":7,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2783"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%B7%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hero"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"protagonist"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"heroic, courageous","examples":[{"text":"عُذْرُ الْمَلُومَيْنِ فِيكَ أَنَّهُمَا\n آسٍ جَبَانٌ وَمِبْضَعٌ بَطَلُ"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be valiant, to be heroic"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become null, void, futile, worthless, pointless","examples":[{"text":"إِذَا عُرِفَ السَّبَبُ بَطَلَ الْعَجَبُ.","english":"When the reason is known, the wonder is lost."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to nullify, to invalidate, to render ineffective, to rescind, to repeal, to revoke"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of بَطَلَ (baṭala) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"masculine plural of بَاطِل (bāṭil)","tags":["form-of","masculine","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *baṭal-.\n\nThe verb form I is inherited from Proto-Semitic *baṭal-.\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2783","headword_ar":"بَطَلَ","root":"bTl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buTolN","text_ar":"بُطْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buTuwlN","text_ar":"بُطُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buTolaAnN","text_ar":"بُطْلَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [of which the last seems to be the most common,] (S, Msb, K, KL, &c.,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baATil","text_ar":"بَاطِل"},{"kind":"text","text":", as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haq~","text_ar":"حَقّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) [i. e.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, false, untrue, wrong"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incorrect, fictitious, spurious, unfounded, unsound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vain, unreal, naught, futile, worthless, useless, unprofitable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL, PS,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"devoid of virtue"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"efficacy, ineffectual, null, void, of no force,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of no account;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it went for nothing, as a thing of no account,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as a thing that had perished"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"become lost."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) [It is said of an assertion or allegation and the like, and of a deed, &c.] Hence the saying in the Kur [vii. 115],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa baTala maA kaAnuwA yaEomaluwna","text_ar":"وَ بَطَلَ مَا كَانُوا يَعْمَلُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And what they were doing became vain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"null;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went for nothing, as a thing of no account"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damuhu buTolFA","text_ar":"دَمُهُ بُطْلًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His blood went for nothing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unretaliated, and uncompensated by a mulet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as a thing of no account."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTala damuhu","text_ar":"بَطَلَ دَمُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[signifies the same; or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was slain without there being obtained for him either blood-revenge or blood-wit."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA.) ―         -b2-  See also the inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buTuwlN","text_ar":"بُطُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baT~aAlN","text_ar":"بَطَّالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labaTula Alqawolu","text_ar":"لَبَطُلَ القَوْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How false, untrue, wrong"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incorrect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is the saying!"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said in wonder at that which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baATil","text_ar":"بَاطِل"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTala","text_ar":"بَطَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTala mina AlEamali","text_ar":"بَطَلَ مِنَ العَمَلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTaAlapN","text_ar":"بَطَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, KL) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biTaAlapN","text_ar":"بِطَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is mentioned by one of the expositors of the Mo'allakát, and said to be the more chaste, and sometimes one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buTaAlapN","text_ar":"بُطَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", to make it accord with its contr."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumaAlapN","text_ar":"عُمَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a hired man, or hireling,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, idle, unoccupied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without work."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, * K, KL. [See also 5.]) [Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomu baTaAlapK","text_ar":"يَوْمُ بَطَالَةٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A day of idleness; a holiday."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biTaAlapN","text_ar":"بِطَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr, also signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being diverted from that which would bring profit in the present life or in the life to come."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-  See also 2. ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTala fiY Hadiyvihi","text_ar":"بَطَلَ فِى حَدِيثِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; so it seems to be from the context in the K, but correctly"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTila","text_ar":"بَطِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the Jm; (TA;) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTaAlapN","text_ar":"بَطَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) [and app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buTuwlN","text_ar":"بُطُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also; see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baT~aAlN","text_ar":"بَطَّالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He jested,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"joked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was not serious"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in earnest, in his discourse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AbTl","text_ar":"ابطل","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTula","text_ar":"بَطُلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTaAlapN","text_ar":"بَطَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, KL) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biTaAlapN","text_ar":"بِطَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Msb, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buTaAlapN","text_ar":"بُطَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buTuwlapN","text_ar":"بُطُولَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, KL,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, courageous, brave,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stronghearted, on the occasion of war,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fight; such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTalN","text_ar":"بَطَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.; (S, Msb, K, KL;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tbT~l","text_ar":"تبطّل","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or this last signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he affected courage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constrained himself to be, courageous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta$aj~aEa","text_ar":"تَشَجَّعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labaTula Alr~ajulu","text_ar":"لَبَطُلَ الرَّجُلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How courageous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is the man!"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said in wonder at"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~abaT~ul","text_ar":"التَّبَطُّل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. courage, &c., or the affecting of courage, &c.]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","KL","PS","TA","Lth"]}]}}